---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PaintedHighlight from "../components/PaintedHighlight.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Story — Erlon Rachi"
  description="First-person narrative: where Erlon comes from, what he believes, what he's doing now."
>
  {/* Inline SVG duotone filter: maps grayscale of portrait to Europa Blue Deeper
      (shadows) → Paper (highlights). Engraving / lithograph register. */}
  <svg style="position: absolute; width: 0; height: 0;" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
    <defs>
      <filter id="duotone-europa" color-interpolation-filters="sRGB">
        <feColorMatrix type="matrix" values="
          0.299 0.587 0.114 0 0
          0.299 0.587 0.114 0 0
          0.299 0.587 0.114 0 0
          0     0     0     1 0
        "/>
        <feComponentTransfer>
          <feFuncR tableValues="0.031 0.718"/>
          <feFuncG tableValues="0.078 0.725"/>
          <feFuncB tableValues="0.161 0.749"/>
        </feComponentTransfer>
      </filter>
    </defs>
  </svg>

  <main class="story mx-auto max-w-[860px] px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="label-mono">Story</p>
    <h1 class="display-xl story__h1">
      <PaintedHighlight>Building people</PaintedHighlight> before building code.
    </h1>

    {/* ---------- Beat 1: Where I come from (with portrait) ---------- */}
    <section class="beat beat--with-portrait">
      <p class="label-mono beat__label">01 / Where I come from</p>
      <div class="beat__grid">
        <figure class="portrait">
          <img
            src="/img/erlon-portrait.jpg"
            alt="Erlon Rachi"
            class="portrait__img"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            width="560"
            height="700"
          />
        </figure>
        <div class="beat__prose">
          <p>
            Applied math at UNICAMP. The operating years. The philosophy of building people before building code.
          </p>
          <p>
            Italian citizen, born in a small village in Brazil. I left that village to study at the best university in the country. I have worked in top companies across the US, Brazil, the UK, and the EU.
          </p>
          <p>
            I built teams. I mentored people into senior leadership positions. I have changed lives. Over the last ten years, I have created more than <strong>USD 250MM in value</strong> for the clients and employers who trusted me with the work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ---------- Beat 2: What I believe ---------- */}
    <section class="beat">
      <p class="label-mono beat__label">02 / What I believe</p>
      <div class="beat__prose">
        <p>
          AI can bring out the best of us. People and organisations stand to benefit greatly from it, when it is built with care.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is why I support the European principles of explainability, responsibility, and accountability in how AI is designed and deployed. I follow stoicism in practice. I am a deep humanist in instinct.
        </p>
        <p>
          The future I am building toward is <PaintedHighlight>a more prosperous, fairer society</PaintedHighlight>. AI is the vehicle, not the destination.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ---------- Beat 3: What I'm doing now ---------- */}
    <section class="beat">
      <p class="label-mono beat__label">03 / What I'm doing now</p>
      <div class="beat__prose">
        <p>
          I am building organisations that are AI-native, including my own firm, Iarandu. The current bet is on problems that make people and organisations benefit from the potential of AI without surrendering judgment to it.
        </p>
        <p>
          The operating thesis behind everything I do is simple: <PaintedHighlight>data and knowledge are more important than software</PaintedHighlight>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ---------- Beat 4: How I work (spec sheet) ---------- */}
    <section class="how-i-work">
      <p class="label-mono beat__label">04 / How I work</p>
      <dl class="spec-sheet">
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Cadence</dt>
          <dd>Sync. Daily standup pattern.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Style</dt>
          <dd>Direct but diplomatic. 100% transparency, no sugar-coating. Respectful of how the information lands.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Trust</dt>
          <dd>Trust, but verify.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Posture</dt>
          <dd>Hands-on. I gravitate to problems I genuinely enjoy: behavioural analysis, data modelling, agentic systems design.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Method</dt>
          <dd>Socratic in conversation. DevOps in delivery. Incremental improvement, learning from results.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Pace</dt>
          <dd>Fast. Sprint-based. I sharpen the axe before cutting.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Expects from client</dt>
          <dd>Genuine interest in the solution. The access and authority needed to get the work done.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Geography</dt>
          <dd>No timezone restriction. Milan-based, with clients and partners served across the US and Australia.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    {/* ---------- Practical close ---------- */}
    <footer class="practical">
      <dl class="spec-sheet spec-sheet--compact">
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Location</dt>
          <dd>Milan. 100% open to relocate for the right long-term engagement.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Languages</dt>
          <dd>Portuguese and English native. Italian beginner.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Timezone</dt>
          <dd>CET. No operational restriction.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <dt class="label-mono">Reach</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/erlonrachi/" rel="me noopener">LinkedIn</a>
            <span style="color: var(--paper-muted);"> · </span>
            <a href="/work-with-me">contact form</a>
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>

      <p class="practical__epigraph">
        Nothing that is worth doing can be done alone.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .story__h1 {
    margin: 14px 0 80px;
    max-width: 18ch;
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .story__h1 {
      margin-bottom: 112px;
    }
  }

  .beat {
    margin-top: 88px;
  }

  .beat:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .beat__label {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .beat__prose p {
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--paper-soft);
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .beat__prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .beat__prose strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  /* Beat 1 layout: portrait + prose 2-col on desktop, stack on mobile */
  .beat--with-portrait .beat__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .beat--with-portrait .beat__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
      gap: 44px;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1000px) {
    .beat--with-portrait .beat__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
      gap: 56px;
    }
  }

  .portrait {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .portrait__img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    max-width: 280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    filter: url(#duotone-europa);
    /* Subtle border in europa-blue-mid to anchor against the dark surface */
    border: 1px solid var(--border-soft);
  }

  /* How I work spec sheet — same pattern as /work intro spec */
  .how-i-work {
    margin-top: 112px;
    padding-top: 56px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
  }

  .spec-sheet {
    margin: 32px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-medium);
  }

  .spec-sheet--compact .spec-row {
    padding: 12px 0;
  }

  .spec-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 18px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-medium);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .spec-row {
      grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
      gap: 32px;
    }
  }

  .spec-row dt {
    padding-top: 2px;
    color: var(--paper-muted);
  }

  .spec-row dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--paper-soft);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .spec-row a {
    color: var(--paper);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent-link);
    transition: text-decoration-color 140ms;
  }

  .spec-row a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--splash);
  }

  /* Practical close + epigraph */
  .practical {
    margin-top: 112px;
    padding-top: 32px;
  }

  .practical__epigraph {
    margin: 64px 0 0;
    padding-top: 32px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    font-family: "Newsreader", Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2vw, 26px);
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--paper);
    max-width: 36ch;
    text-align: left;
  }

  /* Print: remove duotone filter on portrait, keep everything else legible */
  @media print {
    .portrait__img {
      filter: none;
    }
  }
</style>
